.DS_Store
*.bak

# Rust / Cargo build artifacts (M0-02-T01).
/target
# M2-02 iOS cross-compile artifacts (XCFramework staging + libvokra.a per triple).
# The build/ tree is produced by scripts/build-ios.sh; it is not committed —
# CI regenerates it, releases upload the .xcframework as a Release asset.
/build/
# M2-11 Unity UPM package tarball artifacts (produced by
# scripts/build-unity-package.sh). CI regenerates and release.yml uploads
# these as Release assets; do not commit.
bindings/unity/*.tgz
bindings/unity/*.tgz.sha256
# M2-12 Python bindings: bytecode cache, egg-info, build outputs, and the
# CI-injected prebuilt native library payload. Wheels are produced by
# cibuildwheel in release.yml and uploaded to PyPI + GH Releases.
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.egg-info/
bindings/python/build/
bindings/python/dist/
bindings/python/src/vokra/_lib/*.so
bindings/python/src/vokra/_lib/*.dylib
bindings/python/src/vokra/_lib/*.dll
# Isolated integration workspaces (integrations/*) build to their own target/.
# Their Cargo.lock IS committed (reproducible opt-in builds); only artifacts are
# ignored. These crates are excluded from the root workspace (zero-dep invariant).
integrations/**/target/

# M3-11 Godot GDExtension AssetLib package artifacts (produced by
# scripts/build-godot-gdextension.sh). CI regenerates and release.yml uploads
# these as Release assets; do not commit.
/dist/godot/
# M3-11-T12: per-target flat staging tree used by the CI crossbuild matrix
# (godot-crossbuild.yml uploads one artifact per Rust triple). Produced by
# scripts/build-godot-gdextension.sh; never committed.
integrations/vokra-godot/pkg/

# NOTE: Cargo.lock is intentionally COMMITTED (CI reproducibility) and must
# not be ignored — see docs/adr/0001-crate-layout.md.

# Claude Code: the shared config (.claude/settings.json) and .claude/skills/
# ARE committed as project policy; only personal/local overrides are ignored.
.claude/settings.local.json

# Client-private planning docs — removed from the repo AND from git history on
# 2026-07-04 (maintainer decision). Kept locally as the source of truth; must
# NOT be re-added to git / made public. Covers the 4 design docs, the internal
# research set, and the CLAUDE.md project guide (internal planning notes).
# Local Claude Code still reads the on-disk CLAUDE.md.
/CLAUDE.md
/docs/requirements.md
/docs/system-requirements.md
/docs/deliverables.md
/docs/milestones.md
/docs/_research/
# Second batch (2026-07-04): internal PM tickets, ADRs, and research/integration
# summaries — kept local, removed from the repo AND git history.
/docs/tickets/
/docs/adr/
/docs/onnx-alternative-research.md
/docs/piper-plus-integration.md
# Third batch (2026-07-19): the M4-residual audit report. Same class as the
# tickets/ADRs above — an internal PM artefact (42-row CC backlog with effort
# estimates, the owner-only queue, cost lines) that was swept into an
# unrelated fixtures commit rather than added deliberately, and that nothing
# in the repo references. It also records an unremediated licence-gate
# fail-open and cites ~20 paths that do not exist publicly, so publishing it
# would both disclose that and 404 for every reader. Untracked BEFORE it ever
# reached origin/main, so no history rewrite was needed.
/docs/m4-residual-audit-2026-07-19.md
# Fourth batch (2026-07-20, M5-10/11-MATERIAL T01 default proposal — owner
# ratifies via T05(iv); see docs/adr/M5-10-11-material-pack.md Decision 2):
# the EU legal-consultation evidence pack and the funding-pitch bench pack are
# internal material for the owner critical path (M5-10 EU cert / M5-11 seed).
# The evidence pack cites gitignore-local docs (milestones.md / system-
# requirements.md line numbers that 404 in a public clone) and catalogues
# compliance gaps (watermark embedding deferred, disclosure enforcement
# unwired); the pitch pack's numbers are already public but its funding framing
# (positioning / seed size / competitor strategy) is internal. Same class as
# the m4-residual audit above. Numbers stay sourced from the tracked
# docs/bench-baselines/*/report.md; external-deck transcription needs owner
# sign-off (T05(iii)).
/docs/legal/
/docs/bench-baselines/pitch-*/

# M4-01: wasm build artifacts (produced by scripts/build-wasm.sh; the npm
# package assembles them at release time — never committed)
/web/dist/
/web/pkg/*.wasm
/web/pkg/vokra_webgpu.js
/web/pkg/vokra_worker.js
/web/pkg/LICENSE
/web/pkg/NOTICE
# Locally staged/converted model files (scripts/fetch-demo-models.sh,
# tools/wasm/run-whisper-wasm.mjs recipe) — GGUFs are never committed.
/models/
# npm pack output from local dry-runs.
/web/pkg/*.tgz
# Unity WebGL staticlib staged by scripts/build-unity-webgl-lib.sh (M4-02) —
# native binaries are assembled by CD, never committed (CHANGELOG "Not
# included"; only .gitkeep + the hand-authored .meta are tracked).
/bindings/unity/com.vokra.unity/Plugins/WebGL/libvokra.a
